## Additional Terms for Research Use

This project is intended for educational and research purposes. Commercial use
is permitted under the MIT license terms, but users are encouraged to:

1. Respect privacy and obtain appropriate consent when deploying positioning systems
2. Follow applicable local laws and regulations regarding WiFi monitoring
3. Use the technology responsibly and ethically
4. Contribute improvements back to the open source community

## Attribution

If you use this research in academic work, please cite:

```
WhoFi: WiFi-Based Indoor Positioning Research
https://github.com/jedarden/whofi
```

And reference the original WhoFi paper:

```
Avola, D., Pannone, D., Montagnini, D., & Emam, E. (2025). 
WhoFi: Deep Person Re-Identification via Wi-Fi Channel Signal Encoding. 
arXiv preprint arXiv:2507.12869.
```